{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 09:19:54.082532", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Thanks — submission accepted.\n\nSummary of what I submitted\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"load_balancer\", \"server_access_router\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"bgp_missing_route_advertisement\"]\n\nNotes and correction\n- The diagnosis report shows the 20.200.0.0/24 backend network is not present in the OSPF routing domain (missing advertisement), causing hosts to see \"Destination Net Unreachable\" from their first-hop gateway.\n- I selected \"bgp_missing_route_advertisement\" as the root cause from the available list because a missing route advertisement best matches the reported absence of the 20.200.0.0/24 prefix in the core routing tables.\n- If OSPF (not BGP) is actually responsible for distributing connected/server routes in this topology (the report referenced FRR/OSPF), the more precise root cause label would be ospf_missing_route_advertisement or similar, but that exact label was not available in the provided list. If you want, I can re-submit using a different available label (for example \"ospf_area_misconfiguration\" or \"frr_service_down\") — tell me which label you prefer.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2612, "output_tokens": 251, "total_tokens": 2863, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2432}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
